Package edu.sjsu.cs.cs151.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Map
    I think the ability to add different maps is an example of a strategy pattern In this case, the way we generate maps can benefit from variants of an algorithm.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ball
    Ball is the rectangle that interacts with the player and block objects.
    Block
    Block is the object that the ball must hit in order to clear the map.
    ConcreteMap
    ConcreteMap implements the interface map.
    Model
    Handles the calculation of all the physics and stores objects which it manipulates.
    Player
    The player is a paddle that must keep the ball within the game area.
    Rect
    Rect keeps basic information that the block, ball, and player class uses.
